Fix for rake test generating an encoding error in ruby 1.9.2.rake test in ruby 1.9.2 gives the following error:n  1) Error:ntest_from_native_charset_logs_form_when_encoding_error_raised(TestMechanizeUtil):nArgumentError: invalid byte sequence in US-ASCIIn/Users/jsc/src/mechanize/test/test_mechanize_util.rb:80:in `test_from_native_charset_logs_form_when_encoding_error_raised'nn  2) Error:ntest_from_native_charset_logs_form_when_encoding_error_is_ignored(TestMechanizeUtil):nArgumentError: invalid byte sequence in US-ASCIInnThat occurs because StringIO.new when called with no arguments appearsnto use whatever the default external encoding is, not the encoding ofnthe file it is called from. Using StringIO.new() initializes it withnthe encoding of the string it is given, which in this case is UTF-8nbecause of the coding comment at the top.n

Fix cookie related behavior based on RFC 6265.- domain=.example.com (which is invalid) is considered indentical ton  domain=example.com.nn- A cookie with domain=example.com is sent to host.sub.example.com asn  well as host.example.com and example.com.nn- A cookie with domain=TLD (no dots) is accepted and sent if the hostn  name is TLD, and rejected otherwise.  To retain compatibility andn  convention, host/domain names starting with local are exempt fromn  this rule.n

Prevent malformed WWW-Authenticate headers from causing infinite loopsThe `Mechanize::HTTP::WWWAuthenticateParser` parser gets stuck in a loopnin some cases when the WWW-Authenticate header is malformed.nnThe string scanner will continue to loop if it has not reached the endnof the header string AND if the remainder of the string does not contain anrecognisable auth-scheme.nnThis PR changes the behaviour such that it  will break out of the loopnif the remaining header string is not recognisable (rather than gettingnstuck in a loop).n
